I've been to Zuuk about 3 times. First time, I was there for the grand opening at Aventura Mall. Zuuk was one of the 3 vendors that were open at that time in the new "Food Hall". The concept is, in a nutshell, "create your own bowl" which is currently the craze in SoFlo but this place offers a Mediterranean flare. I created my own bowl with bulgur wheat, roasted red pepper hummus, mint tzatziki, zahtar feta, baked falafel and topped it off with a bunch veggie toppings. It was definitely a filling meal for around 10 bucks. For my 2nd and 3rd visit, I basically had the same concoction but with chicken. The reason why I stuck to the falafel and chicken was that they charge an extra $2 for the lamb, beef or seasonal veggies. Don't get me wrong, the bowls I had were delicious but I can't justify the extra $$ for what they consider an upgrade from the chicken while other similar joints like Bolay offer 2 proteins with all the fixings for $10. Nevertheless, the food quality at Zuuk's was great so that's why I kept coming back. Plus, it's also a healthier option compared to the typical Chinese or Pizza normally found in food courts.  I just have a couple of suggestions. The staff needs to pay close attention to the display. The last time I came, the rice and bulgur wheat were merely empty so they looked burnt and dry sticking at the bottom of the pots. 3 people in front of me said the same thing and they left because it didn't look fresh. In addition, the dips and spreads need to be even out constantly because they don't look enticing when you see the craters from the scoops are all over the place. I think, they should be treated like gelato or ice cream. I have worked in the food industry before and I've learned that first impression, especially presentation, is one way to entice the guest to want more food :)
